<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Leaders keep on talking
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Peace talks between Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak
and Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat took an interesting turn last
week _ the two leaders met alone.
</P>
<P>
   Barak and Arafat arrived Tuesday at Camp David, the president's
private retreat in Maryland. They hope to overcome differences that
have prevented peace in their region. Normally, President Clinton
or Secretary of State Madeleine Albright have attended these
meetings to help negotiate sticky issues, such as creating borders
for a future independent Palestinian state.
</P>
<P>
   But Wednesday, the two leaders met without a U.S. negotiator.
The meeting is being taken as a sign that the men are serious about
coming to a peace agreement.
</P>
<P>
   MILLENNIAL KIDS LOOKING GOOD
</P>
<P>
   Millennial kids appear to be doing better than children who came
before them, according to a government report. Millennial kids are
defined as those born since 1982.
</P>
<P>
   The report says the number of children who live in poverty and
the number who die young have fallen to their lowest levels in 20
years. Teenage pregnancy and juvenile violence also reached their
lowest rates.
</P>
<P>
   Even though rates dropped overall, poor and minority children
were more likely to die young, become pregnant as teenagers and be
involved in violence.
</P>
<P>
   The annual report is compiled by the Federal Interagency Forum
on Child and Family Statistics. Millennials are the largest
generation of children in American history with more than 70
million kids.
</P>
<P>
   BOBBY COX SUSPENDED
</P>
<P>
   Atlanta Braves manager Bobby Cox may have to watch his team play
the Tampa Bay Devil Rays on television from home tonight. Cox was
handed a five-game suspension last week after he bumped umpire
Derryl Cousins on July 4 in a second-inning dispute. The manager
argued with Cousins when the umpire gave catcher Fernando Lunar a
warning for not lining up in the catcher's box. During the
argument, Cox seemed to nudge Cousins' elbow. Cox planned to appeal
the suspension.
</P>
