   DRUG-ARREST (Washington) _ For nearly six years, a man suspected
of murdering an American anti-narcotics agent in 1994 was the
perfect fugitive, melting into a 19th century Mexican world that
kept him well-hidden. 1,000 words. By Chris Marquis.
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-METRIC (Rotherham, England) _ The British have had ample
warning about the coming of metrification. But small shopkeepers
like Keane Fletcher, a butcher, are refusing to go along in an
illustration of British resistance to the ways of Europe. 1,100
words. By Sarah Lyall.
</P>
