   LOBBYING-BROTHERS (Washington) _ Call it Podesta vs.
podesta.com. John D. Podesta, chief of staff at the White House, is
trying to secure a legacy for President Clinton by adding
prescription drug benefits to Medicare and by enacting a bill of
rights for patients. His brother, Anthony T. Podesta, a lobbyist
for the drug industry, is working against him. Tony Podesta, the
older brother, represents the Pharmaceutical Research and
Manufacturers of America, a trade association for drug companies
that opposes the president's Medicare plan. One of Tony Podesta's
partners, Jeff Ricchetti, represents the Blue Cross and Blue Shield
Association, a trade group in the forefront of the insurance
industry's efforts to kill the patient's rights bill favored by
Clinton. Jeff's older brother, Steve Ricchetti, is John Podesta's
deputy at the White House. 1,500 words. By Robert Pear and John M.
Broder.
