r l BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     07-16 0752
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 Copyright 2000 Chronicle Publishing Company 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ONCE YOU GET TO KNOW HIM &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The Washington Post got hold of a persuasive fund-raising letter
for the Clinton Presidential Library in downtown Little Rock, was
 &LR; written by former Sen.  &UR; Dale Bumpers &LR; , D-Ark. The longtime pal of
the president included the following irresistible pitch:
</P>
<P>
   ``We shouldn't let our familiarity with  &UR; Bill Clinton &LR;  stop us
from appreciating the depth and range of his accomplishments as
president.''
</P>
<P>
   P.S. The Washington Monthly says that  &UR; George W. Bush &LR;  defeated
a candidate who later beat Bill Clinton. Bush won an election for
seventh-grade class president over &UR; Jack Hanks &LR; , who years later
beat  &UR; Bill Clinton  &LR; in an election for vice president of Boys
Nation, an American Legion youth group.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BEYOND SEX &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Ellen DeGeneres &LR; , who's about to begin a nationwide tour doing
stand-up comedy, told People magazine she is tired of being defined
as a lesbian.
</P>
<P>
   ``I needed to express myself again because my sexuality had
overshadowed so much of my life,'' she said. ``I'm not trying to
make you forget, but I want my audience to come see me because I'm
going to do a comedy show. It's not a rally. ... Maybe I'll become
the Artist Formerly Known as Lesbian.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE OUT-OF-IT GUIDE TO AD HOMINEM GOSSIP &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Is  &UR; Judge Judy &LR;  on the Supreme Court?'' ( &UR; Rob De Witt &LR;  and
 &UR; Michael Slaughter &LR; ). ``And what's all this noise about an M&AMP;M
wrapper?'' ( &UR; Jay Hipps &LR; ). ``And what ever happened to  &UR; Regis &LR; 
 &UR; Philbin &LR; ?'' ( &UR; Bob Wieder &LR; ).
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NO WELCOME MAT FOR HARRY POTTER &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Canterbury Cathedral officials have rejected Warner Bros.'
request to shoot some of its Harry Potter movie in the cathedral.
The problem, reports the Daily Mail of London, is that the story
uses pagan  &LR; images of witchcraft and wizardry.
</P>
<P>
   ``For ourselves,'' said a spokesman for the Rev.  &UR; John &LR; 
 &UR; Simpson &LR; , ``we did not think the books posed problems. But other
people might take offense, and so we had to say no.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CARROTS AND STICKS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   A South Bay reader is wondering about that big Silicon Valley
bash to raise money for education and featuring  &UR; Colin Powell &LR; , at
which the entertainment was provided by a band called was &LR;  the
Cherry Poppin' Daddies. Is the name some kind of message to the
young 'uns?
</P>
<P>
   And a guest at the grand reopening of the Wax Museum is
complaining because the figure of former  &UR; President Bush &LR;  in a
gallery of U.S. presidents is labeled ``George W. Bush.'' Walker is
the former president's middle name, but it's his son who's usually
labeled ``W,'' unless paraffin psychics can see the future.
</P>
<P>
   Finally, in response to  &UR; Chelsea Clinton &LR;  having been spotted
smoking at a Washington coffee shop over July Fourth weekend, a
group of young people _ mainly Libertarians, says the Washington
Times _ held a smoke-in in Washington last week. ``We are not
necessarily condoning smoking,'' said one organizer. ``We want to
emphasize that an adult's decisions regarding health and morality
should be left to that person only.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BODILY FUNCTIONS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Prince Ernst  &LR; of Monaco, who is married to  &UR; Princess Caroline &LR; ,
has apologized for urinating publicly in Turkey's pavilion at a
world's fair in Germany. ``Relieving myself during Expo 2000 was
definitely not a conscious act,'' he said, his words of regret
reported in Us Weekly.
</P>
<P>
   ``Saturday Night Live'' regular  &UR; Will Ferrell &LR; , on the other
hand, told Entertainment Weekly that if he could have one
superpower, he would like ``the power to vomit on people on
command. It would help me get out of tight situations.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``I was at a  &UR; Versace &LR;  party and ran into a modeling agent who
... told me that I should be an actress. ... Then I went to an
ashram a week later and did this meditation and hiking thing. While
I was there,  &UR; Steven Spielberg &LR; 's office called my agent and wanted
to know if I act. I was like, `This is a sign from God.' I called
the acting coach and started taking her class. When I did did a
memory exercise, she started crying and told me that I have to use
my instrument, that if I don't do something creative I will hurt
myself or someone else. ... I said, `You're right. You're f_
right.''
</P>
<P>
   -  &UR; Amber Valetta &LR;  _ who appears in the forthcoming ``What Lies
Beneath'' _ on her metamorphosis from supermodel to actress, in
Movieline magazine.
</P>
</TEXT>
