<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Bored no more! Game board book thrills on long rides
 &HT;    By Theresa Walsh Giarrusso
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Even though I'm not a kid, I still get bored on long
car trips. So during a recent ride to Florida, I tested out ``The
Amazing Game Board Book,'' by Shereen Gertel Rutman and illustrated
by John Clementson.
</P>
<P>
   This 36-page hardback ``book,'' published by Innovative Kids,
features more than 50 games and activities. When you unhook the
magnetic cover, you'll find a foam Chinese checker board on the
left, along with other peg board games. Underneath is a compartment
to store the pegs, an erasable felt-tip pen, magnetic checkers and
magnetic puzzle pieces.
</P>
<P>
   Flip through the colorful book on the right side and you'll
find: crosswords, a puzzle, geography games about the United
States, coded messages, brain teasers, math puzzles, labyrinths,
Dominoes, a solar system game and an erasable drawing board.
</P>
<P>
   Whew! Plenty to do for an eight-hour car ride!
</P>
<P>
   For some of the games, you need two people to play, so it's
perfect if you're stuck in the backseat with a brother or sister.
Or get the whole family involved and multiply your fun.
</P>
<P>
   Tell your parents the durable ``Amazing Game Board Book'' is
well worth the $19.99 price tag. You'll be so engaged by the book's
challenges, you'll finally stop asking ``Are we there yet?''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
