<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MIDEAST-SUMMIT-0717-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Tensions Increase as Mideast Peace Talks Continue
 &HT;    By Bob Deans and Larry Kaplow
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   THURMONT, Md. President Clinton met into the night Sunday with
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat, as Mideast peace talks at Camp
David lumbered through their sixth inconclusive day.
</P>
<P>
   In a reminder of the issues and passions at stake, more than
100,000 Israeli demonstrators rallied in Tel Aviv to protest
Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak's approach to the peace process.
</P>
<P>
   And in Washington, Senate Majority Leader Trent Lott, R-Miss.,
warned that the Republican-led Congress would not give Clinton a
blank check to pay for pledges he might make to secure a Mideast
peace accord.
</P>
<P>
