<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Monday, July 17 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact William Toren at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   DNC-SPONSORS (Los Angeles) _ Big-name politicians and big-name
corporations are part of the mix for the Democratic National
Convention. AT&AMP;T is contributing $1 million in long-distance
service, Hilton Hotels is donating lodging, General Motors is
offering free cars and limos. Many companies contribute to both
national conventions and cite a sense of civic activism as their
motivation. But not everyone is convinced. By Bill Hillburg. (Will
move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   CIGARETTE-IMPORTS (Los Angeles) _ Exploiting costly tobacco
industry settlements that have boosted brand-name cigarette prices,
a chain of cigarette stores has been selling foreign brands for as
much as $10 less per carton than American labels. Smokers are
lighting up with joy, but U.S. tobacco companies are fuming that
foreign and small manufacturers are taking unfair advantage of the
fact that they're exempt from paying the big settlements. By Steve
Carney and Benjamin Parke. (Will move in the ``a'' national and
``n'' California news files.)
