<HEADLINE>
BEG YOUR PARDON, MR. CRUTCH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Please, Jerry West, don't go.
</P>
<P>
   Please, the Lakers need you.
</P>
<P>
   Please, you can't leave.
</P>
<P>
   (Ahem ... pause for effect) ...
</P>
<P>
   Please, Jerry, stay around another season.
</P>
<P>
   Please, keep making those big deals to keep the Lakers on that
championship run.
</P>
<P>
   Please, please, (begin ital)puuulll(end ital)eeeezzzz ...
</P>
<P>
   (Is this convincing enough yet? How much longer do we have to
keep this up?) ...
</P>
<P>
   So please ... stop making us beg you to stay year after year.
It's getting embarrassing, as much as you seem to need to hear it
every summer.
</P>
<P>
   If you're gonna quit, then quit. We understand.
</P>
<P>
   If you're gonna stay, stay.
</P>
<P>
   Now take this paper, wrap up the fish you just brought back from
Alaska, and get back in your office. ...
