<P>
   SAFRICA-EBONY-MEDIA (Durban, South Africa) _ After five years
struggling to generate revenue, the South African edition of Ebony
magazine has shut down. Although the United States edition is still
sold here, the failure of the local edition is a sign of the
slower-than-hoped-for growth of a black South African upper-middle
class. By Henri E. Cauvin.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-POLITICS-MEDIA (Undated) _ In the experimental
environment of Internet-based political information, two commercial
Web sites, including one whose news operation is directed by the
prominent journalist Carl Bernstein, are covering the upcoming
elections and political conventions while maintaining partnerships
under contract with the political parties. By Rebecca Fairley
Raney.
